    "bpm": 120.0,
    "name": "Arp Pluck",
    "notes": "Keyboard-driven arpeggiator. Hold a chord and the Arpeggiator plays it one note at a time (Up, 2 octaves, 1/16 at 120 BPM) on its own internal clock. Arp Frequency -> Saw oscillator, Arp Gate -> plucky ADSR shaping the amplitude, into a resonant low-pass and a short delay for echoes. Wire a Clock node into the Arp's Clock input to sync to a tempo instead.",
